> native\xunit.console.netcore.exe

@ericstj I tried this, but it didn't work.  The file gets listed in project.lock.json as expected, but the ResolveNuGetPackageAssets task doesn't deploy anything from a native folder that's not specific to a runtime.  The logic is in [GetCopyLocalItems](https://github.com/dotnet/roslyn-internal/blob/275671ee97283bbff71b59e173ed9319ac415b83/Closed/MSBuildNuGet/Tasks/ResolveNuGetPackageAssets.cs#L234).

I'm not sure a fix for this would go entirely in the task, either.  You'd need to define what happens when you have a native folder that's specific to a runtime a runtime-agnostic one.  Should you take all files from both (preferring the runtime-specific ones when there is the same file in both places), or should the existence of a runtime-specific native folder mean the runtime-agnostic folder isn't used at all?  That type of decision seems like maybe it should be part of NuGet instead of the ResolveNuGetPackageAssets task.
